Creating an AI-based financial advisor website with a chatbot, login, register, and dashboard pages is a complex task that requires a comprehensive approach. I'll provide a high-level overview of the project and some sample code to get us started.

Project Overview

To build an AI-based financial advisor website, we'll need to integrate several components:

Frontend: A user-friendly interface built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, where users can interact with the chatbot and access their dashboard.
Backend: A server-side application built using a programming language like Node.js, Python, or Ruby, which will handle user authentication, data storage, and chatbot logic.
Chatbot: A conversational AI built using a library like Dialogflow, Botpress, or Rasa, which will provide financial advice and guidance to users.
Database: A database management system like MySQL, MongoDB, or PostgreSQL, which will store user data, financial information, and chatbot conversations.
